        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 24 at 1:49PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 149 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Bernice, or 13 miles north of Grambling, moving
northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Farmerville, Bernice, Cooley, Dubach, Marion, Vienna, Lisbon,
Bayou D Arbonne Lake, Shiloh, D Arbonne, Unionville, Linville,
Cecil, Mount Zion, Corinth, Litroe and Haile.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
